> Separately, is there a readthedocs.io page for this repo?

Nope, and it's intentional. We only created this library to help legacy first-party clients (notably google-api-python-client and temporarily google-cloud-python) move from oauth2client to google-auth. We're actively discouraging the continued use of httplib2.

@dan-blanchard as a mere user, I don't have a strong opinion on the tags thing--I just want something that will work for the platforms I care about (cp35-cp35m-manylinux1) that's integrated into the main release, so that I can eventually get it into at least my pants install.

That said, it looks like explicitly defining the full platform tag (analogous to gcc platform triples) is the way to go rather than assume some decomposition will work (combinatorial explosion + implicit pickup of new platforms from combinations). The space of platforms of built wheels is pretty sparsely populated at least from my casual look at pypi so it's not an issue to manually specify each platform at least for the initial version of this feature.

